<!Doctype html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Simple Selectors</title>
<style>/*Element Selector*/
p{
color: blue;
}
/*ID selector*/
#main{
color: red;
}
/*Class selection*/
.note{
color: green;
}
/*Group selector*/
h1,h2{
text-align: center;
}
/*Universal selector*/
*{
font-family: Arial;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1 id="main">CSS SELECTORS</h1>
<h2>INTRODUCTION</h2>
<p>SELECTOR FORMS.</p>
<p class="note">A CSS selector is used to select HTML elements so that we can apply styles (color , size , layout, etc.)to them.</p>
</body>
</html>

